<!-- body="start" -->
Forwarded message:<br>
<i>&gt; From owner-cypherpunks@toad.com Fri Dec  1 15:55 EST 1995</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Forwarded message:</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; From: "Bob Bruen, MIT Lab for Nuclear Science" &lt;BRUEN@mitlns.mit.edu&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;   The following came from a government source. I thought it might be of</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;   interest. </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;                        Bob</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; --------------------------------------------------------------------------</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;      At yesterdays FNC  (Federal Networking Council) meeting it was </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;      mentioned in passing that NSA has given Netscape a grant of $5 Million </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;      (yes $5M) to beef up the security features of Netscape. More info will </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;      be forthcoming on this.</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
